<h1>Random Acts of Kindness Everywhere User Data Deletion Instruction</h1>
<h4>Effective Date: September 1, 2021</h4>
 
<p>We at Random Acts of Kindness Everywhere #RAKE  (R.A.K.E. "we" "us" or "our") know you care about how your Personal Information (as defined below) is used and shared, and we take your privacy seriously. Please read the following to learn more about our Privacy Policy. By using or accessing the Network in any manner, you acknowledge that you accept the practices and policies outlined in this Privacy Policy, and you hereby authorize RAKE to collect, use, and share your Personal Information for the purposes and in a manner consistent with terms set forth herein.
 
<h4>We currently operate in the United States only.</h4>
 
<h4>Security of Your Personal Information</h4>
 
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Security. The security of the information that identifies, relates to, describes, is capable of being associated with, or could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, with a particular consumer or household that you provide to us ("Personal Information") is extremely important to RAKE. We use physical, electronic, and administrative safeguards that are designed to protect your Personal Information from loss, misuse unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration and destruction. Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. While we do our best to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee the security of your Personal Information. Any transmission of Personal Information is at your own risk. We are not responsible for circumvention of any privacy settings.</p>
 
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Children Under the Age of 13. The Network is not intended for children under 13 years of age, and we do not knowingly collect Personal Information from children under 13. If we learn we have collected or received Personal Information from a child under 13 without verification of parental consent, we will delete that Personal Information. If you believe we might have any Personal Information from or about a child under 13, please contact us at info@rakenow.org. California residents under 16 years of age may have additional rights regarding the collection and sale of their Personal Information. Please see Your California Privacy Rights for more information.</p>
 
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Notice of Breach of Security. If a security breach causes an unauthorized intrusion into the Network that materially affects you, RAKE will notify you as soon as possible and later report the action we took in response.</p>
 
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Safeguarding Your Personal Information. We take reasonable and appropriate measures to protect Personal Information from loss, misuse and unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration and destruction, taking into account the risks involved in the processing and the nature of the Personal Information. Kindli accounts require a username and password to log in. You must keep your username and password secure, and never disclose it to a third party. Account passwords are encrypted, which means we cannot see your passwords. We cannot resend forgotten passwords either. We will only reset them.</p>
 
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Data Retention. In accordance with and as permitted by applicable laws and regulations, we will retain your Personal Information as long as necessary to provide the Network to you, to maintain your account for as long as your account is active, or as otherwise needed to operate our business. We may not accommodate a request to change Personal Information if we believe the change would violate any law or legal requirement or cause the Personal Information to be incorrect. If you delete your Content from the Network, copies of your Content may remain viewable in cached and archived pages, or might have been copied or stored by other Network users. Proper access and use of information provided on the Network, including Content, is governed by our terms of use.</p>

<h4>Personal Information We Collect</h4>
 
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Account Information: If you sign up for or authenticate into an account with us, we may collect information that you provide to us in connection with setting up the account, such as your username, name, email address and, for an account you authenticate into, role ("Account Information"). Further, in the course of using your account, you may provide us with additional Account Information through your communications with us.</p>
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Payment Information: We may ask you to provide certain information, including your name, address, email, and credit card information (collectively "Payment Information"), in connection with processing your transactions. You may update your Payment Information through your account. All credit card processing for the Network is handled directly a third party provider (and any Personal Information you provide governed by its privacy policy). Your Payment Information is encrypted and transmitted directly and securely to our payment processors and is not stored on our systems.</p>
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Personal Information from Third Parties: We may receive Personal Information related to your use of other websites and applications including your username, name, email address, shipping address and your interaction with these third parties. Common examples include signing up for a group, registering for an event.From time to time, we may also receive contact enrichment information from third parties.</p>
<p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;Usage Data: We may also automatically collect certain usage information when you access the Network ("Usage Data"), such as your Internet Protocol address ("IP address"), information derived from your IP address such as your geographic location, log files, unique device identifiers, pages viewed, browser type, any links you click on to leave, and other usage information collected from cookies and other tracking technologies. We collect IP addresses to track and aggregate non-personal information, such as monitoring the regions from which users navigate to the Network. We also collect IP addresses from users when they log into the Network as part of our log-in and security features. We may also, when you enable location-based services, collect Global Positioning System (GPS) location data and/or motion data. We may also collect transactional behavior conducted by users on the Network when tied to personal identifiers.</p>
<p>Feedback: You may provide us with feedback regarding the Network (e.g., in the form of email, suggestions for how to improve the Network, etc.). We do not delete this information.</p>



